page.title: 09EXETER CANAL
page.content: 235 ships passed through the Double Locks from May 1984 to May 1985. Many of these used the lock in groups. Small light craft like canoes are carried along the canal bank. We picked specimens from 48 different plants between the river and the canal. There were 19 different wild plants between Topsham Road and the river. We caught two small dace; there were also sticklebacks, minnows pike bream roach, carp, eels, perch, millers' thumbs and stone leach. There are hedgerow birds and water birds, like heron and kingfisher. We see Winter migrants like redshanks and gooseanders.
